{"TopicId":104060,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mod for making prograde vector visible outside of map view","CreatedByName":"jarmund","CreatedById":126888,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-13T18:11:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"jarmund","CreatedById":126888,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-13T18:11:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI remember seeing a video of Scott Manley using a mod while flying that allowed him to see the prograde vector and heading when not in map view. Unfortunately I have been unable to find this video again, and I cannot remember the name of the specific mod I wanted.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere were two mods:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E- One that showed all vectors (prograde, retrograde, normal, radial, etc) in addition to the axi of these\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E- One that only showed prograde, your heading, in addition to an artificial horizont.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI would like to try both of them, so does anyone know which mods I\u0027m talking about?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-04-13T18:19:55Z\u0022 title=\u002204/13/2015 06:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EApril 13, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by jarmund\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Harry Rhodan","CreatedById":119953,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-13T18:52:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIs it \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/81543\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ENavHud\u003C/a\u003E?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jarmund","CreatedById":126888,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-04-13T18:54:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Harry Rhodan\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Harry Rhodan\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EIs it \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/81543\u002